> add requestBaseUrl to SolrClient and default implementation should throw UnsupportedOperationException.

I think I agree with David - it feels weird to add methods that would throw UOE in the majority of implementations.  It'd be right at home in other languages I think (Python, for instance), but cuts against expectation here IMO.

That said, I share @iamsanjay 's dislike for having the concrete type creeping into a lot of these usage locations.  Would a sub-class / sub-interface here be helpful?  e.g.

```
interface UrlOverrideableSolrClient {
  ...
  SolrResponse requestWithUrl(String, SolrRequest);
}
```

Something like the above would let users convey that they need "one of those clients that supports alternate URLs" without needing to specify the exact concrete type.  Something to consider for a followup JIRA/PR if you guys think it makes sense...
